<figureCitation box="[353,401,1592,1618]" captionStart="FIGURES 130–133" captionStartId="97.[151,269,1626,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1602]" captionTargetId="figure-58@97.[150,1438,194,1602]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURES 130–133. Male genitalia of the Indo-Malayan species of Scolytocis Blair showing the Y-shaped ninth segment (ix), tegmen (teg) and penis (pen). 130. Scol. malayanus sp. nov. 131. Scol. philippinensis sp. nov. 132. Scol. thayerae sp. nov. 133. Scol. werneri sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5127103" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5127103/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">130</figureCitation>
